summaries.short: As Christopher recovers from shell shock, a round of vicious rumors leads to a shocking tragedy at Groby, his family home.
summaries.full: As Christopher recovers from shell shock in France, a round of vicious rumors leads to a shocking tragedy at Groby, his family home. Sylvia finds a new admirer, Brownlie; Edith and Macmaster plan a new life together; Valentine, whose family has been stigmatized, secures a London teaching job, but falls out of favor with the social-climbing Edith.

summaries.short: Sylvia visits Christopher in France; later, his leniency towards a deserter and his contradiction of an officer have dire consequences.
summaries.full: In Rouen, Christopher prepares recruits for battle. Bored in London, Sylvia decides to visit her husband in France, oblivious to the consequences. Christopher's leniency towards a soldier accused of desertion angers the chief of military police. Following a confrontation outside Sylvia's hotel room, Christopher is ordered to leave Campion's training unit--for the front.

summaries.short: Sylvia and Christopher reconcile and move to a flat opposite Macmaster; later, Christopher enlists in the army, infuriating his wife.
summaries.full: After a stint in France with her fawning admirer, Perowne, Sylvia reunites with Christopher. Under his terms of reconciliation, Christopher insists they move into a flat opposite Macmaster. After war is declared, Christopher is ordered to massage military numbers; outraged at being asked to lie, he quits his job and enlists in the army, infuriating his wife.

summaries.short: Christopher takes over at the front; later, he is sent home where Sylvia tries to keep her husband from building a future with Valentine.
summaries.full: At the front, Christopher takes over from a commanding officer who suffers from shell shock and a drinking problem. After General Campion arrives to take over his command, Christopher convalesces and is sent home, where Sylvia--now ensconced at Groby--makes a last-ditch attempt to keep her husband from building a future with Valentine.

summaries.short: Principled aristocrat Christopher Tietjens enters into a destructive marriage with a cruel socialite, but vows to stay faithful.
summaries.full: In the dying days of the Edwardian Empire, principled aristocrat Christopher Tietjens enters into a destructive marriage with cruel socialite Sylvia (Rebecca Hall), despite learning that the baby she carries may not be his. Christopher resolves to remain faithful, even after encountering Valentine Wannop, a fearless young suffragette with whom he shares an instant connection.
